\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93We should make time for it,\u8221\'94 said Obo, annoyed. \u8220\'93See, you hate the Hrkan Lords, I understand that, but if you want to see Hrk destroyed, ending Solraheen won\u8217\'92t do it. Solraheen is merely a symbol in this age. You do understand that He\u8217\'92s buried under a mountain of rock?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I do,\u8221\'94 said Ayram.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93And you understand that the Lords keep Him sedated on safee fumes so that he can\u8217\'92t talk? He hasn\u8217\'92t said a word in centuries.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Killing Him might stir up chaos for a few years, but it won\u8217\'92t do a thing to change the balance of power. There\u8217\'92s a good chance, with how tightly the Lords control access to Solraheen, that they could hide his death for as long as they wished. Either way, Hrk will remain Hrk, and whatever side you\u8217\'92re on will still look and feel like\u8230\'85\u8221\'94 Obo gestured broadly at the rubble around him, and at the pile of bodies. \u8220\'93It will feel like }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1 this}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 .\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}}